<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Our bid reflects our deeply held belief that c=
ustomers should come first. Rather than having their assets liquidated for =
cash, our bid permits users to retain their cryptocurrencies and empowers t=
hem to make future decisions on what they want do with THEIR assets.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">New to Binance.US customers will have access t=
o our suite of products &amp; services, such as ~150 different cryptocurren=
cies, 300 trading pairs, 5,000+ convert pairs, industry-leading low fees, i=
ncl. 0 fee BTC &amp; ETH trading &amp; the largest US on-chain staking plat=
form. ...</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">We always maintain 1:1 reserves, and are subje=
ct to regular audits and regulatory reporting by government entities. We do=
 not offer margin products, undertake proprietary trading, or take on any c=
orporate debt.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Binance.US is well capitalized: our assets exc=
eed our liabilities. All of our customers could withdraw their assets tomor=
row, which is their right &amp; we would still have hundreds of millions of=
 current assets. =E2=80=A6</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">We will do everything in our power to speed up=
 the legal and court approval process. =C2=A0Current target, pending court =
approvals, is to provide users access to their assets in March, 2023.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Presumably Binance.US is sharing those audits =
and those balance sheets with the bankruptcy court. Voyager has already bee=
n burned once.</p>
